\hypertarget{function-to-clean-tweet-text}{%
\subsubsection{Function to clean Tweet
Text}\label{function-to-clean-tweet-text}}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\KeywordTok{library}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"stringr"}\NormalTok{)}

\NormalTok{clean_tweet_text <-}\StringTok{ }\ControlFlowTok{function}\NormalTok{(unclean_tweet) \{}


\NormalTok{  clean_tweet =}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"&amp"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, unclean_tweet)}
\NormalTok{  clean_tweet =}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"(RT|via)((?:}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{b}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{W*@}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{w+)+)"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, clean_tweet)}
\NormalTok{  clean_tweet =}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"@}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{w+"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, clean_tweet)}
  \CommentTok{# clean_tweet = gsub("[[:digit:]]", "", clean_tweet)}
\NormalTok{  clean_tweet =}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"[ }\CharTok{\textbackslash{}t}\StringTok{]\{2,\}"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, clean_tweet)}
\NormalTok{  clean_tweet =}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"^}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{s+|}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{s+$"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, clean_tweet)}

 \CommentTok{# Remove emojis}
\NormalTok{  clean_tweet <-}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{'}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{p\{So\}|}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{p\{Cn\}'}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{''}\NormalTok{, clean_tweet, }\DataTypeTok{perl =} \OtherTok{TRUE}\NormalTok{)}
    
  \CommentTok{# Remove the urls}
\NormalTok{  clean_tweet <-}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{str_replace_all}\NormalTok{(clean_tweet, }\StringTok{"https://t.co/[a-z,A-Z,0-9]*"}\NormalTok{,}\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{  clean_tweet <-}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{str_replace_all}\NormalTok{(clean_tweet, }\StringTok{"http://t.co/[a-z,A-Z,0-9]*"}\NormalTok{,}\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{)}

  \CommentTok{#Remove hashtags}
  \CommentTok{#clean_tweet <- str_replace_all(clean_tweet,"#[a-z,A-Z]*","")}

  \CommentTok{# Remove newlines (\textbackslash{}n)}
\NormalTok{   clean_tweet <-}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"[}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}r\textbackslash{}n}\StringTok{]"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{" "}\NormalTok{, clean_tweet)}
   
   \CommentTok{# Remove all dots and dashes}
    \CommentTok{#clean_tweet =  gsub("\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}.", " ", clean_tweet, perl=TRUE)}
    \CommentTok{#clean_tweet =  gsub("\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}-", " ", clean_tweet, perl=TRUE)}
    \CommentTok{#clean_tweet =  gsub("\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{},", " ", clean_tweet, perl=TRUE)}
    \CommentTok{#clean_tweet =  gsub("\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}:", " ", clean_tweet, perl=TRUE)}
    \CommentTok{#clean_tweet =  gsub("\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}?", " ", clean_tweet, perl=TRUE)}
    \CommentTok{#clean_tweet = gsub("[[:punct:]]", "", clean_tweet)}
    

  \CommentTok{# Remove additional spaces}
\NormalTok{    clean_tweet =}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"(?<=[}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{s])}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{s*|^}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{s+|}\CharTok{\textbackslash{}\textbackslash{}}\StringTok{s+$"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, clean_tweet, }\DataTypeTok{perl=}\OtherTok{TRUE}\NormalTok{)}
    
    \KeywordTok{return}\NormalTok{(clean_tweet)}

\NormalTok{\}}

\NormalTok{clean_text <-}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{clean_tweet_text}\NormalTok{(unclean_tweet)}

\NormalTok{clean_text}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

             \DataTypeTok{data =}\NormalTok{ char_lenDF,}
             \DataTypeTok{lambda =} \KeywordTok{seq}\NormalTok{(}\OperatorTok{-}\DecValTok{6}\NormalTok{,}\DecValTok{6}\NormalTok{,}\FloatTok{0.1}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{             )}

\NormalTok{Cox2 =}\StringTok{ }\NormalTok{Cox[}\KeywordTok{with}\NormalTok{(Cox, }\KeywordTok{order}\NormalTok{(}\OperatorTok{-}\NormalTok{Cox}\OperatorTok{$}\NormalTok{Box.y)),]}

\NormalTok{Cox2[}\DecValTok{1}\NormalTok{,]}

\hypertarget{kruskal-wallis-post-hoc-tests-after-nemenyi}{%
\subsubsection{Kruskal-Wallis -- post-hoc tests after
Nemenyi}\label{kruskal-wallis-post-hoc-tests-after-nemenyi}}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\KeywordTok{library}\NormalTok{(PMCMR)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\begin{verbatim}
## Registered S3 methods overwritten by 'PMCMR':

\end{verbatim}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{char_lenDF}\OperatorTok{$}\NormalTok{country <-}\StringTok{ }\KeywordTok{as.factor}\NormalTok{(char_lenDF}\OperatorTok{$}\NormalTok{country)}
\KeywordTok{posthoc.kruskal.nemenyi.test}\NormalTok{(char_lenDF}\OperatorTok{$}\NormalTok{text_length, char_lenDF}\OperatorTok{$}\NormalTok{country, }\DataTypeTok{data =}\NormalTok{ char_lenDF, }\DataTypeTok{dist =} \StringTok{"Tukey"}\NormalTok{)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}
